From 02b6b46d5c8a33f58f62cbfa3899f36122c650b5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gaoyang Zhang <younglobalization@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 02:26:11 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] vendor(openclaw): hide media tool model overrides

Why:
- RivonClaw CS raw-mode agents should use configured image/video models and must not invent unsupported per-call media model overrides.
- The image and video_generate tool schemas exposed free-form model fields that agents could fill with incompatible models, causing media tool failures.

Removal:
- Drop when upstream OpenClaw removes agent-facing media tool model overrides or safely validates unsupported overrides against configured media model defaults.

Tests:
- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-tools.config.ts src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.test.ts
